	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In my experience using this in duels, about five <BR>
or six casts will drain a level 50ish caster so <BR>
figure in the neighborhood of one bar per cast on <BR>
a level 50.  Scale it up accordingly as your opponent<BR>
drops in level.  Most 50's have around 2200 to 2400<BR>
mana so figure a drain of 400 mana per cast or <BR>
thereabouts.  This spell does NOT repeat does NOT<BR>
give you mana in return.  In fact, since it takes<BR>
mana to cast MS, by the time I drain a level 50 of<BR>
all his mana, I'm usually down to 1/3 to 1/2 of my<BR>
mana also.  I, however, have something called clarity<BR>
which they don't.  <BR>
<BR>
As for use against NPCs, I never ever cast this. NPCs<BR>
have way too much mana for this to be of use.  It may <BR>
take 10 casts to drain one and by that time I'm oom <BR>
myself and the fight has probably been over long before<BR>
anyway.  <BR>
<BR>
Where I've heard it's useful is against Lady Vox. Get<BR>
two or three enchanters off to the side casting MS<BR>
on her nonstop while the others tank and nuke.  She<BR>
complete heals herself if given the chance and I have<BR>
read 3 enchanters chain casting MS can drain a good <BR>
deal of her mana reserves.  Never done Vox myself <BR>
so don't know if this is true or BS.  Nonetheless, <BR>
the only time I use MS is in duels against other <BR>
casters and it's this  spell, plus mez, that makes<BR>
us so feared in PVP against other spell slingers. <BR>
<BR>
BTW, in ruins of Kunark expansion, there is a level <BR>
55ish spell planned that DOES drain 450 mana and <BR>
give it to the enchanter.  It has a recast time of <BR>
like 15 minutes though so don't plan on chain casting<BR>
it for infinite reward.  
				</font>
			</td>

